Fresh on the heels of announcing he had signed a deal with Universal Music gospel star Dr.Tumi has said he wants to fill up The Dome. Tumi said he will be joined on stage by other gospel stars in a gathering of worshipers on August 20.It will be recorded for a live DVD.Tumi said that the massive concert is just the cherry on top of a great 2017.He announced at an event that he had signed a deal with Universal Music and was also in talks to work with international stars.&#8220;To be in partnership with such a massive record label is a dream come true.&#8221;&#8220;It&#8217;s time our music goes out onto a global stage &#8221; he said at the event.He said that his aim for the concert is to unite as many people as he can through praise music.